{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"35d3c311-5d77-4682-a9f2-8a72fecb0e44","content":"The `.testsettings` format is **legacy and ignored by modern MSTest/VSTest**. You need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file. Here's what your file configures and how each maps:\n\n| `.testsettings` setting | `.runsettings` equivalent |\n|---|---|\n| `TestTimeout=30000` | `<MSTest><TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` |\n| Code coverage data collector | `<DataCollectors>` section |\n| `AssemblyResolution/useLoadContext` | Default in modern MSTest — not needed |\n\nLet me create the migrated files:","toolRequests":[{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01T9H3yhivjzpD5TW22HmCBG","name":"report_intent","arguments":{"intent":"Creating runsettings migration"},"type":"function"},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01QwZ7o5wpHWMYZHRoz86pbL","name":"create","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9f5117fdd3c843519cd2a8c460161aa1/local.runsettings","file_text":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?>\n<RunSettings>\n  <RunConfiguration>\n    <TestSessionTimeout>300000</TestSessionTimeout>\n  </RunConfiguration>\n\n  <MSTest>\n    <!-- Per-test timeout in milliseconds (was TestTimeout in .testsettings) -->\n    <TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>\n  </MSTest>\n\n  <DataCollectionRunSettings>\n    <DataCollectors>\n      <DataCollector friendlyName=\"Code Coverage\"\n        uri=\"datacollector://Microsoft/CodeCoverage/2.0\"\n        assemblyQualifiedName=\"Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector.CoverageCollectorDataCollector, Microsoft.VisualStudio.TraceCollector, Culture=neutral\">\n      </DataCollector>\n    </DataCollectors>\n  </DataCollectionRunSettings>\n</RunSettings>\n"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"create a new file at /tmp/sv-9f5117fdd3c843519cd2a8c460161aa1/local.runsettings."},{"toolCallId":"toolu_vrtx_01F6GdCHUKSudSCWYY18TtkR","name":"edit","arguments":{"path":"/tmp/sv-9f5117fdd3c843519cd2a8c460161aa1/TestProject.csproj","old_str":"  <ItemGroup>","new_str":"  <PropertyGroup>\n    <RunSettingsFilePath>$(MSBuildProjectDirectory)\\local.runsettings</RunSettingsFilePath>\n  </PropertyGroup>\n\n  <ItemGroup>"},"type":"function","intentionSummary":"edit the file at /tmp/sv-9f5117fdd3c843519cd2a8c460161aa1/TestProject.csproj."}],"interactionId":"a4121f29-0a07-4c99-a6c1-1bd7e62d3273","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user has a `.testsettings` file which is the legacy format, and they've upgraded to MSTest 3.8.0. The `.testsettings` format is no longer supported by modern MSTest. They need to migrate to a `.runsettings` file.\n\nLet me create the `.runsettings` equivalent and update the `.csproj` to reference it.\n\nThe `.testsettings` file has:\n1. Assembly resolution with `useLoadContext=\"true\"` — this is default behavior in modern MSTest, no migration needed\n2. `TestTimeout` of 30000ms — maps to `<TestTimeout>30000</TestTimeout>` in `.runsettings` under `<MSTest>` or can use `[Timeout]` attribute. In `.runsettings`, it goes under `<MSTest><TestTimeout>`.\n\n\n3. Code coverage data collector — I need to add a `<DataCollectors>` section to handle this in the `.runsettings` file.\n\nNow I'll create the `.runsettings` file with these settings and update the project file to reference it.","outputTokens":904,"requestId":"3412:2317F5:DFAB94:105924B:69F41097"},"id":"14c3f90e-e6c8-4055-9851-94c007628002","timestamp":"2026-05-01T02:32:04.798Z","parentId":"a6b27217-c29b-4a1d-88ab-49c24b7759bb"}
